Hong Kong Bans South African Poultry Imports Following Avian Flu Outbreak

-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 
2011-04-13T13:21:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/hong-kong-bans-south-african-poultry-imports-following-avian-flu-outbreak.html
Hong Kong ’s Center for  Food Safety 
said it suspended processing applications for imports of
poultry, game birds and their products from  South Africa .  The decision follows confirmation of outbreaks of avian flu
at ostrich farms in South Africa’s Western Cape province, the
organization said in a statement published on its website today.
The Center for Food Safety is seeking further information from
government authorities on the situation, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  